h: variant of   Barrett  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":29,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Barrett Of Bellhouse In Aveley was born in 1353, in Bellhouse, Essex, England. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth Norton. He died in 1400, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1353–1400":"1353–1400","1355–1380":"1355–1380","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1400":"1400","1355":"1355","1353":"1353","1440":"1440","21 Sep 1380":"21. september 1380","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Minsterworth, Gloucestershire, England":"Minsterworth, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bellhouse, Essex, England":"Bellhouse, Essex, England"},"fi":{"1353–1400":"1353–1400","1355–1380":"1355–1380","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1400":"1400","1355":"1355","1353":"1353","1440":"1440","21 Sep 1380":"21. syyskuuta 1380","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Minsterworth, Gloucestershire, England":"Minsterworth, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bellhouse, Essex, England":"Bellhouse, Essex, England"},"fr":{"1353–1400":"1353–1400","1355–1380":"1355–1380","138